sols_latex:
Using implicit differentiation, we solve for the derivative of y in both
curves

\begin{align*}
xy &= a \\
y + xy' &= 0\\
y' &= \frac{-y}{x}
\end{align*}

and for the second curve,

\begin{align*}
x^2 - y^2 &= b  \\
2x - 2yy' &= 0\\
2(x - yy') &= 0\\
x - yy' &= 0\\
y' &= \frac{x}{y}
\end{align*}

These two slopes are negative reciprocals of each other. Hence, if the
curves intersect each other, they do at a right angle.

